If no otherwise stated, all the files in this directory are released
under a MIT-style license: see LICENSE file for details.

If you want to use kim-os as a whole operating system, please include LICENSE
file in your project's repository, and/or publish or redistribute it if
you're delivering and/or selling it to someone else.

If you just want to copy some files of kim-os project, you just have
to declare the kim-os origin at top of the file. Just retain the header as-is:

"This file is part of kim-os project: https://github.com/colosimo/kim-os
 According to kim-os license, you can do whatever you want with it,
 as long as you retain this notice."

If you copy one or more files and then modify them, please declare that they
were originally part of kim-os.
